    "THE MIDLAND JOURNAL PUBLISHED EVERY FRIDAY MORNING BY EWTCNO BROS RISING SUN CECIL COUNTY MARYLAND Entered as Second Class Matter at Post Office In Rising Bun Maryland Under Act of Congress of March 8 1879 INDEPENDENT IN POLITICS AND ALL OTHER SUBJECTS TERMS OF SUBSCRIPTION ONE YEAR IN ADVANCE SO SIX MONTHS THREE MONTHS 1 SINGLE COPY 8 CENTS ADVERTISING RATES FURNISHED ON APPLICATION f THEAMERicANR 1 SSASSOC At ION FRIDAY AUGUST 21 I 9 There are many false prophets but none as far wrong as those who predict that some day radio will sup plant the newspaper both from a news and advertising standpoint Owners of radio sets may not have given the matter much thought but if asked to give up one or the other they would quickly take out their radio There is no question but the printed word always will have an advantage over the spoken word o During the years from 1930 to 1934 there was no sadder reading than the business and financial magazines They were full of news and practically all of the news was bad Their charts of business ac tivity were lower than a snake s belly as the slang phrase"
